				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">well from my personal perspective i think what would be an improvement in future mmorpg's is customization. to be able to customize everything within reach about your character meanwhile keeping the game balanced. it goes as such in life. if people are too alike things get boring. i see it the same way in a game. if there is someone that looks just like me. acts just like me and is as powerful as me that doesnt make my persona in the game very unique now does it?  
<br />

<br />
i am a gamer that is into longevity over graphics, however. i rather have a game with lame graphics that keeps me entranced in it for years upon years rather than a game with mind boggling graphics that gets boring after the second month of game play. a lot of gamers place too much emphasis on graphics.  i'm not gonna pay 12.99 a month to look at my screen in awe. i'm gonna pay 12.99 a month to play a game that allows me to strive to be a great and powerfully unique character.
<br />

<br />

<br />
just my 2 cents worth..</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
